{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01RFrGsRfeEV4pRQdgLesagF","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.coffeeshop.orders.web;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.ws.rs.ApplicationPath;\n     4→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Application;\n     5→\n     6→@ApplicationPath(\"/api\")\n     7→public class RestApp extends Application {}\n     8→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c8c0436c-69f4-4378-aa8f-dd3eb0ddb087","uuid":"cbc7204f-f369-4320-a627-8127935a3b57"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_019D35topJFMjctYEAdSnmyE","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.coffeeshop.orders.web;\n     2→\n     3→import com.coffeeshop.common.domain.OrderRequest;\n     4→import com.coffeeshop.orders.service.OrderService;\n     5→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     6→import jakarta.validation.Valid;\n     7→import jakarta.ws.rs.Consumes;\n     8→import jakarta.ws.rs.GET;\n     9→import jakarta.ws.rs.POST;\n    10→import jakarta.ws.rs.Path;\n    11→import jakarta.ws.rs.PathParam;\n    12→import jakarta.ws.rs.Produces;\n    13→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n    14→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response;\n    15→\n    16→import java.util.Map;\n    17→\n    18→@Path(\"/orders\") // if you already have @ApplicationPath(\"/api\"), change this to just \"/orders\"\n    19→@Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    20→@Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    21→public class OrdersResource {\n    22→\n    23→  @Inject OrderService orderService;\n    24→\n    25→  @POST\n    26→  public Response create(@Valid OrderRequest request) {\n    27→    String id = orderService.place(request); // <-- calls your service\n    28→    // use 202 if you treat it as async, 201 if you consider it created now\n    29→    return Response.accepted(Map.of(\"id\", id)).build();\n    30→  }\n    31→\n    32→  @GET\n    33→  @Path(\"/{id}\")\n    34→  public Response get(@PathParam(\"id\") long id) {\n    35→    // if you already have a repository method, reuse it here\n    36→    // shown minimal for completeness\n    37→    return Response.ok(Map.of(\"id\", id)).build();\n    38→  }\n    39→}\n    40→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c8c0436c-69f4-4378-aa8f-dd3eb0ddb087","uuid":"f1176c3a-c423-4daa-9abd-07408c4c90b7"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01YMeXUrDMUB947uTx7G41aE","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.coffeeshop.orders.api;\n     2→\n     3→import com.coffeeshop.common.domain.OrderAck;\n     4→import com.coffeeshop.common.domain.OrderRequest;\n     5→import com.coffeeshop.orders.domain.OrderEntity;\n     6→import com.coffeeshop.orders.domain.OrderRepository;\n     7→import com.coffeeshop.orders.service.OrderService;\n     8→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     9→import jakarta.ws.rs.*;\n    10→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n    11→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response;\n    12→\n    13→@Path(\"/orders\")\n    14→@Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    15→@Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    16→public class OrdersResource {\n    17→\n    18→    @Inject OrderService orderService;\n    19→    @Inject OrderRepository repo;\n    20→\n    21→    @POST\n    22→    public Response place(OrderRequest req) {\n    23→        String id = orderService.place(req);\n    24→        return Response.accepted(new OrderAck(id)).build();\n    25→    }\n    26→\n    27→    @GET @Path(\"/{id}\")\n    28→    public OrderEntity status(@PathParam(\"id\") long id) {\n    29→        return repo.find(id);\n    30→    }\n    31→}\n    32→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c8c0436c-69f4-4378-aa8f-dd3eb0ddb087","uuid":"c3bb31c4-0c51-4532-ab79-22107b99f92f"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01ECt1SdAzBEhdFzG4PA2r4T","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good, now let me apply all the Java source edits. There are two `OrdersResource` classes (one in `api` and one in `web` package) which will conflict. I need to remove one. I'll keep the `api` one (it's more complete with repo injection) and remove the duplicate `web.OrdersResource`. Also need to handle the two `Application` classes.\n\nIn Quarkus, `@ApplicationPath` works fine. I'll keep one Application class and remove duplicates. Let me consolidate: keep `RestApp` in the `web` package as the single `@ApplicationPath(\"/api\")` and remove `OrdersApplication` in the `api` package. Then keep the `api.OrdersResource` (the more complete one) and remove the `web.OrdersResource`.\n\nActually, looking more closely, having both `@ApplicationPath` classes will cause conflicts in Quarkus. Let me just set the path via `quarkus.rest.path=/api` in application.properties and remove both Application classes. This is cleaner for Quarkus.\n\nLet me now apply all Java source edits:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5703,"cache_read_input_tokens":81938,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":5703,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":2619},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c8c0436c-69f4-4378-aa8f-dd3eb0ddb087","uuid":"2774bdef-75b2-4301-81f4-652885dc7147"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01ECt1SdAzBEhdFzG4PA2r4T","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_0172gnbYkEfGuVAJU11twz3k","name":"Edit","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__coffee-shop__jakarta__quarkus/run_3/output/orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/domain/OrderRepository.java","old_string":"import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport jakarta.persistence.EntityManager;\nimport jakarta.persistence.PersistenceContext;\nimport jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\npublic class OrderRepository {\n\n  @PersistenceContext(unitName = \"ordersPU\")\n  EntityManager em;\n\n  @Transactional\n  public Long save(OrderEntity e){\n    em.persist(e);\n    return e.getId();\n  }","new_string":"import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport jakarta.persistence.EntityManager;\nimport jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\npublic class OrderRepository {\n\n  @Inject\n  EntityManager em;\n\n  @Transactional\n  public Long save(OrderEntity e){\n    em.persist(e);\n    em.flush();\n    return e.getId();\n  }"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5703,"cache_read_input_tokens":81938,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":5703,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":2619},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c8c0436c-69f4-4378-aa8f-dd3eb0ddb087","uuid":"0f0f420a-4f5b-42ae-86d9-4bfc32d3a76c"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01ECt1SdAzBEhdFzG4PA2r4T","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01AwyuBnwkjBsWR81vuuBE3a","name":"Edit","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__coffee-shop__jakarta__quarkus/run_3/output/orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/messaging/OrdersPipeline.java","old_string":"package com.coffeeshop.orders.messaging;\n\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport jakarta.json.bind.Jsonb;\nimport jakarta.json.bind.JsonbBuilder;\nimport org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Channel;\nimport org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Emitter;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\npublic class OrdersPipeline {\n\n  @Inject @Channel(\"barista\")\n  Emitter<String> barista;\n\n  @Inject @Channel(\"kitchen\")\n  Emitter<String> kitchen;\n\n  private static final Jsonb JSONB = JsonbBuilder.create();\n\n  public void publishToBarista(OrderCommand cmd) {\n    System.out.println(\"[orders] sending barista command: \" + cmd);\n    barista.send(JSONB.toJson(cmd));\n  }\n\n  public void publishToKitchen(OrderCommand cmd) {\n    System.out.println(\"[orders] sending kitchen command: \" + cmd);\n    kitchen.send(JSONB.toJson(cmd));\n  }\n\n  // simple DTO for messages\n  public record OrderCommand(String target, long orderId, String item, int quantity) {}\n}","new_string":"package com.coffeeshop.orders.messaging;\n\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.core.JsonProcessingException;\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Channel;\nimport org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Emitter;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\npublic class OrdersPipeline {\n\n  @Inject @Channel(\"barista\")\n  Emitter<String> barista;\n\n  @Inject @Channel(\"kitchen\")\n  Emitter<String> kitchen;\n\n  private static final ObjectMapper MAPPER = new ObjectMapper();\n\n  public void publishToBarista(OrderCommand cmd) {\n    System.out.println(\"[orders] sending barista command: \" + cmd);\n    barista.send(toJson(cmd));\n  }\n\n  public void publishToKitchen(OrderCommand cmd) {\n    System.out.println(\"[orders] sending kitchen command: \" + cmd);\n    kitchen.send(toJson(cmd));\n  }\n\n  private String toJson(Object obj) {\n    try {\n      return MAPPER.writeValueAsString(obj);\n    } catch (JsonProcessingException e) {\n      throw new RuntimeException(e);\n    }\n  }\n\n  // simple DTO for messages\n  public record OrderCommand(String target, long orderId, String item, int quantity) {}\n}"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5703,"cache_read_input_tokens":81938,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":5703,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":2619},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c8c0436c-69f4-4378-aa8f-dd3eb0ddb087","uuid":"d1905e5d-27b6-4297-a3aa-ff8c73579343"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01ECt1SdAzBEhdFzG4PA2r4T","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_019H6KHVpBrb1c7fGj3P7EGu","name":"Edit","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__coffee-shop__jakarta__quarkus/run_3/output/orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/messaging/OrderUpdatesListener.java","old_string":"package com.coffeeshop.orders.messaging;\n\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\nimport org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Incoming;\n\nimport com.coffeeshop.common.domain.OrderStatus;\nimport com.coffeeshop.orders.domain.OrderRepository;\nimport jakarta.json.bind.Jsonb;\nimport jakarta.json.bind.JsonbBuilder;\nimport jakarta.json.bind.JsonbConfig;\nimport java.util.Locale;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\npublic class OrderUpdatesListener {\n\n  private static final Jsonb JSONB = JsonbBuilder.create(new JsonbConfig());\n\n  public static final class OrderUpdate {\n    public Long orderId;\n    public String status;\n    public String from;\n  }\n\n  @Inject OrderRepository repo;\n\n  @Incoming(\"order-updates\")\n  @Transactional\n  public void apply(String payload) {\n    try {\n      if (payload == null) return;\n      String json = payload.trim();\n\n      // Unwrap if the payload is a *stringified* JSON object.\n      int safety = 3;\n      while (safety-- > 0\n          && json.length() >= 2\n          && json.charAt(0) == '\"'\n          && json.charAt(json.length() - 1) == '\"') {\n        json = JSONB.fromJson(json, String.class).trim();\n      }\n\n      OrderUpdate evt = JSONB.fromJson(json, OrderUpdate.class);\n      if (evt == null || evt.status == null || evt.orderId == null) {\n        // dev-friendly: ignore malformed/minimal events instead of killing the stream\n        System.err.println(\"[order-updates] ignored event: \" + json);\n        return;\n      }\n\n      var entity = repo.find(evt.orderId);\n      if (entity == null) return;\n      entity.setStatus(OrderStatus.valueOf(evt.status.toUpperCase(Locale.ROOT)));\n\n    } catch (Exception e) {\n      // DEV: log and continue; do not rethrow or the stream will shut down.\n      System.err.println(\"[order-updates] parse/update error: \" + e + \" payload=\" + payload);\n    }\n  }\n}","new_string":"package com.coffeeshop.orders.messaging;\n\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\nimport org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Incoming;\n\nimport com.coffeeshop.common.domain.OrderStatus;\nimport com.coffeeshop.orders.domain.OrderRepository;\nimport java.util.Locale;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\npublic class OrderUpdatesListener {\n\n  private static final ObjectMapper MAPPER = new ObjectMapper();\n\n  public static final class OrderUpdate {\n    public Long orderId;\n    public String status;\n    public String from;\n  }\n\n  @Inject OrderRepository repo;\n\n  @Incoming(\"order-updates\")\n  @Transactional\n  public void apply(String payload) {\n    try {\n      if (payload == null) return;\n      String json = payload.trim();\n\n      // Unwrap if the payload is a *stringified* JSON object.\n      int safety = 3;\n      while (safety-- > 0\n          && json.length() >= 2\n          && json.charAt(0) == '\"'\n          && json.charAt(json.length() - 1) == '\"') {\n        json = MAPPER.readValue(json, String.class).trim();\n      }\n\n      OrderUpdate evt = MAPPER.readValue(json, OrderUpdate.class);\n      if (evt == null || evt.status == null || evt.orderId == null) {\n        System.err.println(\"[order-updates] ignored event: \" + json);\n        return;\n      }\n\n      var entity = repo.find(evt.orderId);\n      if (entity == null) return;\n      entity.setStatus(OrderStatus.valueOf(evt.status.toUpperCase(Locale.ROOT)));\n\n    } catch (Exception e) {\n      System.err.println(\"[order-updates] parse/update error: \" + e + \" payload=\" + payload);\n    }\n  }\n}"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5703,"cache_read_input_tokens":81938,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":5703,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":2619},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c8c0436c-69f4-4378-aa8f-dd3eb0ddb087","uuid":"c8f721ca-918b-4afe-b26f-518a18fa5812"}
