{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01YakoAKWbY1bfemknrsrb2Q","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good news: the application compiled and built successfully. The failure is at runtime due to:\n1. Kafka not being available (host.docker.internal:9092 can't be resolved)\n2. PostgreSQL not available\n\nI need to configure Quarkus to be more lenient with Kafka startup and use a graceful startup. The key issue is that Quarkus SmallRye Kafka tries to eagerly create the consumer and fails. I need to set `quarkus.messaging.kafka.health.enabled=false` (already set) AND configure the messaging to be lazy/graceful.\n\nLet me update the application.properties to handle this:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3047,"cache_read_input_tokens":125096,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3047,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":258},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c8c0436c-69f4-4378-aa8f-dd3eb0ddb087","uuid":"4c98a40f-9da3-43bf-938c-f84775e524ad"}
