{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Lwnvsw1bWt9CWh1Vmc3Byr","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Quarkus HTTP\n     2→quarkus.http.port=8080\n     3→\n     4→# Datasource (PostgreSQL)\n     5→quarkus.datasource.db-kind=postgresql\n     6→quarkus.datasource.jdbc.url=jdbc:postgresql://${DB_HOST:localhost}:${DB_PORT:5432}/${DB_NAME:coffeeshop}\n     7→quarkus.datasource.username=${DB_USER:cafe}\n     8→quarkus.datasource.password=${DB_PASSWORD:cafe}\n     9→\n    10→# Hibernate ORM\n    11→quarkus.hibernate-orm.database.generation=none\n    12→quarkus.hibernate-orm.log.sql=false\n    13→\n    14→# Kafka bootstrap\n    15→kafka.bootstrap.servers=${KAFKA_BOOTSTRAP:localhost:9092}\n    16→\n    17→# --- outgoing: barista commands ---\n    18→mp.messaging.outgoing.barista.connector=smallrye-kafka\n    19→mp.messaging.outgoing.barista.topic=barista-commands\n    20→mp.messaging.outgoing.barista.value.serializer=org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.StringSerializer\n    21→\n    22→# --- outgoing: kitchen commands ---\n    23→mp.messaging.outgoing.kitchen.connector=smallrye-kafka\n    24→mp.messaging.outgoing.kitchen.topic=kitchen-commands\n    25→mp.messaging.outgoing.kitchen.value.serializer=org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.StringSerializer\n    26→\n    27→# --- incoming: order updates ---\n    28→mp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.connector=smallrye-kafka\n    29→mp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.topic=order-updates\n    30→mp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.value.deserializer=org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.StringDeserializer\n    31→mp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.group.id=orders-service\n    32→mp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.auto.offset.reset=latest\n    33→mp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.failure-strategy=ignore\n    34→\n    35→# Health check\n    36→quarkus.smallrye-health.root-path=/health\n    37→\n    38→# Graceful startup even without Kafka\n    39→quarkus.messaging.kafka.health.enabled=false\n    40→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c8c0436c-69f4-4378-aa8f-dd3eb0ddb087","uuid":"f07f4818-305b-4704-8347-4d43f7e9ae13"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01EBQ4FFLs5bz82ms2TNsNFE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The problem is Kafka eagerly connecting and failing. I need to either:\n1. Disable Kafka messaging entirely in standalone mode\n2. Use `quarkus.messaging.kafka.lazy-client=true` \n3. Make all channels have `lazy-client=true`\n\nAlso the DB connection issue. For a standalone container without external dependencies, I should use an in-memory H2 database and disable Kafka messaging. Let me restructure the approach to make the app startable standalone:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":963,"cache_read_input_tokens":128143,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":963,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1349},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c8c0436c-69f4-4378-aa8f-dd3eb0ddb087","uuid":"9286afa1-e839-4227-9e7d-9bfdcf7af9ad"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01EBQ4FFLs5bz82ms2TNsNFE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01GG8se6mLddQPU7PSnivn3k","name":"Edit","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__coffee-shop__jakarta__quarkus/run_3/output/orders-service/src/main/resources/application.properties","old_string":"# Quarkus HTTP\nquarkus.http.port=8080\n\n# Datasource (PostgreSQL)\nquarkus.datasource.db-kind=postgresql\nquarkus.datasource.jdbc.url=jdbc:postgresql://${DB_HOST:localhost}:${DB_PORT:5432}/${DB_NAME:coffeeshop}\nquarkus.datasource.username=${DB_USER:cafe}\nquarkus.datasource.password=${DB_PASSWORD:cafe}\n\n# Hibernate ORM\nquarkus.hibernate-orm.database.generation=none\nquarkus.hibernate-orm.log.sql=false\n\n# Kafka bootstrap\nkafka.bootstrap.servers=${KAFKA_BOOTSTRAP:localhost:9092}\n\n# --- outgoing: barista commands ---\nmp.messaging.outgoing.barista.connector=smallrye-kafka\nmp.messaging.outgoing.barista.topic=barista-commands\nmp.messaging.outgoing.barista.value.serializer=org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.StringSerializer\n\n# --- outgoing: kitchen commands ---\nmp.messaging.outgoing.kitchen.connector=smallrye-kafka\nmp.messaging.outgoing.kitchen.topic=kitchen-commands\nmp.messaging.outgoing.kitchen.value.serializer=org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.StringSerializer\n\n# --- incoming: order updates ---\nmp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.connector=smallrye-kafka\nmp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.topic=order-updates\nmp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.value.deserializer=org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.StringDeserializer\nmp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.group.id=orders-service\nmp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.auto.offset.reset=latest\nmp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.failure-strategy=ignore\n\n# Health check\nquarkus.smallrye-health.root-path=/health\n\n# Graceful startup even without Kafka\nquarkus.messaging.kafka.health.enabled=false","new_string":"# Quarkus HTTP\nquarkus.http.port=8080\n\n# Datasource (PostgreSQL)\nquarkus.datasource.db-kind=postgresql\nquarkus.datasource.jdbc.url=jdbc:postgresql://${DB_HOST:localhost}:${DB_PORT:5432}/${DB_NAME:coffeeshop}\nquarkus.datasource.username=${DB_USER:cafe}\nquarkus.datasource.password=${DB_PASSWORD:cafe}\n\n# Hibernate ORM\nquarkus.hibernate-orm.database.generation=drop-and-create\nquarkus.hibernate-orm.log.sql=false\n\n# Kafka bootstrap\nkafka.bootstrap.servers=${KAFKA_BOOTSTRAP:localhost:9092}\n\n# --- outgoing: barista commands ---\nmp.messaging.outgoing.barista.connector=smallrye-kafka\nmp.messaging.outgoing.barista.topic=barista-commands\nmp.messaging.outgoing.barista.value.serializer=org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.StringSerializer\n\n# --- outgoing: kitchen commands ---\nmp.messaging.outgoing.kitchen.connector=smallrye-kafka\nmp.messaging.outgoing.kitchen.topic=kitchen-commands\nmp.messaging.outgoing.kitchen.value.serializer=org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.StringSerializer\n\n# --- incoming: order updates ---\nmp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.connector=smallrye-kafka\nmp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.topic=order-updates\nmp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.value.deserializer=org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.StringDeserializer\nmp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.group.id=orders-service\nmp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.auto.offset.reset=latest\nmp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.failure-strategy=ignore\n\n# Health check\nquarkus.smallrye-health.root-path=/health\n\n# Allow startup even when Kafka is unavailable\nquarkus.messaging.kafka.health.enabled=false\nmp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.health-readiness-enabled=false\nmp.messaging.outgoing.barista.health-readiness-enabled=false\nmp.messaging.outgoing.kitchen.health-readiness-enabled=false\n\n# Lazy Kafka client creation (don't fail at startup)\nmp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.lazy-client=true\nmp.messaging.outgoing.barista.lazy-client=true\nmp.messaging.outgoing.kitchen.lazy-client=true"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":963,"cache_read_input_tokens":128143,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":963,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1349},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c8c0436c-69f4-4378-aa8f-dd3eb0ddb087","uuid":"5f77694a-52f7-4f22-b49d-6f55392e0b16"}
