{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01Tr4DAEP3VtwKetiFfponwY","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The `smallrye-in-memory` connector isn't available at build time. The in-memory connector is only for tests with `quarkus-test-common`. I need a different approach. Let me go back to using the Kafka connector but with lazy client and proper error handling. The key is to use a different strategy:\n\n1. Keep the Kafka connector but configure it to be lazy and graceful\n2. Or, better: remove the `@Incoming` annotation from `OrderUpdatesListener` and make it not block startup\n\nActually, the correct Quarkus approach is: the `smallrye-in-memory` connector requires the `quarkus-smallrye-reactive-messaging-in-memory` test dependency. But a simpler solution for standalone mode is to just set Kafka retry behavior so it doesn't fail at startup.\n\nLet me look at the actual error again: `No resolvable bootstrap urls given in bootstrap.servers`. The issue is that `host.docker.internal` doesn't resolve. The fix is: use `localhost:9092` as the default Kafka bootstrap (which also won't resolve, but with lazy client it shouldn't fail). Actually, the issue is that the Kafka connector eagerly creates the consumer.\n\nThe real fix for Quarkus + SmallRye Kafka is to enable `quarkus.messaging.kafka.health.enabled=false` and set `mp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.health-readiness-enabled=false`. But the actual failure is the consumer creation, not a health check.\n\nLooking at Quarkus docs more carefully, in Quarkus 3.x, for Kafka, you can set `mp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.retry=true` and `mp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.retry.max-wait=120` to allow the consumer to retry. Or use `quarkus.messaging.kafka.lazy-start.enabled=true`.\n\nLet me take a different approach: just keep the Kafka connector but set a valid localhost fallback and add `quarkus.kafka.health.enabled=false` along with disabling the startup check. The real solution is to not fail if Kafka is unavailable."}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2384,"cache_read_input_tokens":138756,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2384,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1948},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c8c0436c-69f4-4378-aa8f-dd3eb0ddb087","uuid":"29e034ec-8481-4625-9259-062c0ae1c016"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01Tr4DAEP3VtwKetiFfponwY","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01Vog6TGitHLWN4TCFZtvGGm","name":"Edit","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__coffee-shop__jakarta__quarkus/run_3/output/orders-service/src/main/resources/application.properties","old_string":"# ===== Default: H2 in-memory (standalone/testing) =====\nquarkus.datasource.db-kind=h2\nquarkus.datasource.jdbc.url=jdbc:h2:mem:coffeeshop;DB_CLOSE_DELAY=-1\nquarkus.datasource.username=sa\nquarkus.datasource.password=\n\n# ===== \"prod\" profile: PostgreSQL =====\n%prod.quarkus.datasource.db-kind=postgresql\n%prod.quarkus.datasource.jdbc.url=jdbc:postgresql://${DB_HOST:localhost}:${DB_PORT:5432}/${DB_NAME:coffeeshop}\n%prod.quarkus.datasource.username=${DB_USER:cafe}\n%prod.quarkus.datasource.password=${DB_PASSWORD:cafe}\n\n# Hibernate ORM\nquarkus.hibernate-orm.database.generation=drop-and-create\nquarkus.hibernate-orm.log.sql=false\n\n# Use in-memory connector for messaging (no external Kafka needed for standalone)\nmp.messaging.outgoing.barista.connector=smallrye-in-memory\nmp.messaging.outgoing.kitchen.connector=smallrye-in-memory\nmp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.connector=smallrye-in-memory\n\n# ===== \"kafka\" profile: Real Kafka messaging =====\n%kafka.kafka.bootstrap.servers=${KAFKA_BOOTSTRAP:localhost:9092}\n%kafka.mp.messaging.outgoing.barista.connector=smallrye-kafka\n%kafka.mp.messaging.outgoing.barista.topic=barista-commands\n%kafka.mp.messaging.outgoing.barista.value.serializer=org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.StringSerializer\n%kafka.mp.messaging.outgoing.kitchen.connector=smallrye-kafka\n%kafka.mp.messaging.outgoing.kitchen.topic=kitchen-commands\n%kafka.mp.messaging.outgoing.kitchen.value.serializer=org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.StringSerializer\n%kafka.mp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.connector=smallrye-kafka\n%kafka.mp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.topic=order-updates\n%kafka.mp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.value.deserializer=org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.StringDeserializer\n%kafka.mp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.group.id=orders-service\n%kafka.mp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.auto.offset.reset=latest\n%kafka.mp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.failure-strategy=ignore\n\n# Health check\nquarkus.smallrye-health.root-path=/health\nquarkus.messaging.kafka.health.enabled=false","new_string":"# ===== Default: H2 in-memory (standalone/testing) =====\nquarkus.datasource.db-kind=h2\nquarkus.datasource.jdbc.url=jdbc:h2:mem:coffeeshop;DB_CLOSE_DELAY=-1\nquarkus.datasource.username=sa\nquarkus.datasource.password=\n\n# ===== \"prod\" profile: PostgreSQL =====\n%prod.quarkus.datasource.db-kind=postgresql\n%prod.quarkus.datasource.jdbc.url=jdbc:postgresql://${DB_HOST:localhost}:${DB_PORT:5432}/${DB_NAME:coffeeshop}\n%prod.quarkus.datasource.username=${DB_USER:cafe}\n%prod.quarkus.datasource.password=${DB_PASSWORD:cafe}\n\n# Hibernate ORM\nquarkus.hibernate-orm.database.generation=drop-and-create\nquarkus.hibernate-orm.log.sql=false\n\n# Kafka bootstrap\nkafka.bootstrap.servers=${KAFKA_BOOTSTRAP:localhost:9092}\n\n# --- outgoing: barista commands ---\nmp.messaging.outgoing.barista.connector=smallrye-kafka\nmp.messaging.outgoing.barista.topic=barista-commands\nmp.messaging.outgoing.barista.value.serializer=org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.StringSerializer\n\n# --- outgoing: kitchen commands ---\nmp.messaging.outgoing.kitchen.connector=smallrye-kafka\nmp.messaging.outgoing.kitchen.topic=kitchen-commands\nmp.messaging.outgoing.kitchen.value.serializer=org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.StringSerializer\n\n# --- incoming: order updates ---\nmp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.connector=smallrye-kafka\nmp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.topic=order-updates\nmp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.value.deserializer=org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.StringDeserializer\nmp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.group.id=orders-service\nmp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.auto.offset.reset=latest\nmp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.failure-strategy=ignore\n\n# Health check\nquarkus.smallrye-health.root-path=/health\n\n# Disable Kafka health checks and startup checks\nquarkus.kafka.health.enabled=false\nquarkus.messaging.kafka.health.enabled=false\nmp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.health-readiness-enabled=false\nmp.messaging.outgoing.barista.health-readiness-enabled=false\nmp.messaging.outgoing.kitchen.health-readiness-enabled=false"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2384,"cache_read_input_tokens":138756,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2384,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1948},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c8c0436c-69f4-4378-aa8f-dd3eb0ddb087","uuid":"bc714976-efa8-47c5-a055-2ecb8877af9e"}
