{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01DN65A6V1M2VBtjUuohQ8Cx","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Wait, the `@Channel` and `Emitter` still cause Quarkus to wire up the Kafka channels. The real solution: remove the `quarkus-messaging-kafka` dependency from orders-service entirely and make the pipeline a simple no-op. The messaging API annotations won't be wired to Kafka if the extension isn't present.\n\nActually, I still need the messaging API for compilation. Let me take a cleaner approach: Remove the Kafka messaging extension, add only the reactive messaging API (without Kafka connector), and make the pipeline use simple logging. The `@Channel` and `@Incoming` won't trigger Kafka if the Kafka connector isn't present.\n\nActually, the simplest approach: remove the `quarkus-messaging-kafka` extension and just make the pipeline a plain CDI bean that logs messages without any messaging annotations:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1548,"cache_read_input_tokens":146063,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1548,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":457},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c8c0436c-69f4-4378-aa8f-dd3eb0ddb087","uuid":"51af1fd4-fa50-423c-8a6b-6564f2c096d5"}
