{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01JgJKqNJ54HdtKiyJrYaQg9","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I notice a potential issue with the smoke test: the `POST /api/orders` returns a `202 Accepted` with an `OrderAck(id)` but the smoke test checks for the `id` field. The `OrderAck` record has a field called `id` which Jackson will serialize as `{\"id\":\"...\"}` - that should work.\n\nHowever, the `GET /api/orders/{id}` returns an `OrderEntity` which has a `status` field. The smoke test checks for `data.get(\"status\") == \"PLACED\"` which should match `OrderStatus.PLACED`.\n\nThere's also a concern: the `OrdersResource.place()` method calls `orderService.place(req)` which returns a String, but `OrderService.place()` calls `repo.save()` which is `@Transactional`. The `OrdersResource` is not `@Transactional`, but `OrderRepository.save()` is. The `OrderService` isn't `@Transactional` either. The issue is that `OrderService.place()` first calls `repo.save()` (which commits), then publishes to Kafka. The transaction boundaries should be fine for the basic create flow.\n\nLet me also check the ConstraintViolationExceptionMapper to understand validation behavior:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2271,"cache_read_input_tokens":36801,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2271,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":535},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c8c0436c-69f4-4378-aa8f-dd3eb0ddb087","uuid":"26d407d9-499a-4ae9-8210-db0933c08940"}
