{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_011MAxQebcKvpyGhE5igyv8Z","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.coffeeshop.orders.api;\n     2→\n     3→import com.coffeeshop.common.domain.OrderAck;\n     4→import com.coffeeshop.common.domain.OrderRequest;\n     5→import com.coffeeshop.orders.domain.OrderEntity;\n     6→import com.coffeeshop.orders.domain.OrderRepository;\n     7→import com.coffeeshop.orders.service.OrderService;\n     8→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     9→import jakarta.ws.rs.*;\n    10→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n    11→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response;\n    12→\n    13→@Path(\"/orders\")\n    14→@Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    15→@Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    16→public class OrdersResource {\n    17→\n    18→    @Inject OrderService orderService;\n    19→    @Inject OrderRepository repo;\n    20→\n    21→    @POST\n    22→    public Response place(OrderRequest req) {\n    23→        String id = orderService.place(req);\n    24→        return Response.accepted(new OrderAck(id)).build();\n    25→    }\n    26→\n    27→    @GET @Path(\"/{id}\")\n    28→    public OrderEntity status(@PathParam(\"id\") long id) {\n    29→        return repo.find(id);\n    30→    }\n    31→}\n    32→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c8c0436c-69f4-4378-aa8f-dd3eb0ddb087","uuid":"fec19444-d426-452d-bba1-cb17ce366809"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01V3qWDoBmgwP6HwoR5GfdmS","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The issue is with CDI-level bean validation in Quarkus. When `@Valid` is on a CDI bean method parameter (as in `OrderService.place(@Valid OrderRequest req)`), Quarkus uses its own interceptor that processes validation differently. The fix is to either:\n\n1. Move `@Valid` to the JAX-RS resource method parameter (RESTEasy handles it properly)\n2. Remove validation from the service layer\n\nLet me move `@Valid` to the resource and remove it from the service:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1065,"cache_read_input_tokens":77565,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1065,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":739},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c8c0436c-69f4-4378-aa8f-dd3eb0ddb087","uuid":"dd61e522-f40c-4484-a6b1-85563cb76516"}
