{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01T9HPVRvnAhkGYuggxNhuMs","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Quarkus HTTP\n     2→quarkus.http.port=8080\n     3→\n     4→# ===== Default: H2 in-memory (standalone/testing) =====\n     5→quarkus.datasource.db-kind=h2\n     6→quarkus.datasource.jdbc.url=jdbc:h2:mem:coffeeshop;DB_CLOSE_DELAY=-1\n     7→quarkus.datasource.username=sa\n     8→quarkus.datasource.password=\n     9→\n    10→# ===== \"pg\" profile: PostgreSQL (activate with -Dquarkus.profile=pg) =====\n    11→%pg.quarkus.datasource.db-kind=postgresql\n    12→%pg.quarkus.datasource.jdbc.url=jdbc:postgresql://${DB_HOST:localhost}:${DB_PORT:5432}/${DB_NAME:coffeeshop}\n    13→%pg.quarkus.datasource.username=${DB_USER:cafe}\n    14→%pg.quarkus.datasource.password=${DB_PASSWORD:cafe}\n    15→\n    16→# Hibernate ORM\n    17→quarkus.hibernate-orm.database.generation=drop-and-create\n    18→quarkus.hibernate-orm.log.sql=false\n    19→\n    20→# Kafka bootstrap\n    21→kafka.bootstrap.servers=${KAFKA_BOOTSTRAP:localhost:9092}\n    22→\n    23→# --- outgoing: barista commands ---\n    24→mp.messaging.outgoing.barista.connector=smallrye-kafka\n    25→mp.messaging.outgoing.barista.topic=barista-commands\n    26→mp.messaging.outgoing.barista.value.serializer=org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.StringSerializer\n    27→mp.messaging.outgoing.barista.lazy-client=true\n    28→\n    29→# --- outgoing: kitchen commands ---\n    30→mp.messaging.outgoing.kitchen.connector=smallrye-kafka\n    31→mp.messaging.outgoing.kitchen.topic=kitchen-commands\n    32→mp.messaging.outgoing.kitchen.value.serializer=org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.StringSerializer\n    33→mp.messaging.outgoing.kitchen.lazy-client=true\n    34→\n    35→# --- incoming: order updates ---\n    36→mp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.connector=smallrye-kafka\n    37→mp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.topic=order-updates\n    38→mp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.value.deserializer=org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.StringDeserializer\n    39→mp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.group.id=orders-service\n    40→mp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.auto.offset.reset=latest\n    41→mp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.failure-strategy=ignore\n    42→mp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.lazy-client=true\n    43→mp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.retry=true\n    44→mp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.retry.max-wait=60\n    45→\n    46→# Health check - serve at /health (under non-application root /q/)\n    47→quarkus.http.non-application-root-path=/\n    48→quarkus.smallrye-health.root-path=health\n    49→\n    50→# Disable Kafka health/startup/readiness checks so app is UP without Kafka\n    51→quarkus.kafka.health.enabled=false\n    52→mp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.health-readiness-enabled=false\n    53→mp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.health-startup-enabled=false\n    54→mp.messaging.outgoing.barista.health-readiness-enabled=false\n    55→mp.messaging.outgoing.barista.health-startup-enabled=false\n    56→mp.messaging.outgoing.kitchen.health-readiness-enabled=false\n    57→mp.messaging.outgoing.kitchen.health-startup-enabled=false\n    58→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c8c0436c-69f4-4378-aa8f-dd3eb0ddb087","uuid":"b837f130-6775-476c-b7a1-294810e660bf"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01LFgiJottp2nWRoKXSYZNng","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The `health-startup-enabled` property needs to be the correct SmallRye key. Looking at the health output, the startup check is still showing. Let me use the global SmallRye Reactive Messaging health config instead:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1546,"cache_read_input_tokens":81172,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1546,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":548},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c8c0436c-69f4-4378-aa8f-dd3eb0ddb087","uuid":"e04d5c69-1e7f-4335-9aea-9608455a8fa4"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01LFgiJottp2nWRoKXSYZNng","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01AVZTqxBn9Fbf3j8UWduupJ","name":"Edit","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__coffee-shop__jakarta__quarkus/run_3/output/orders-service/src/main/resources/application.properties","old_string":"# Health check - serve at /health (under non-application root /q/)\nquarkus.http.non-application-root-path=/\nquarkus.smallrye-health.root-path=health\n\n# Disable Kafka health/startup/readiness checks so app is UP without Kafka\nquarkus.kafka.health.enabled=false\nmp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.health-readiness-enabled=false\nmp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.health-startup-enabled=false\nmp.messaging.outgoing.barista.health-readiness-enabled=false\nmp.messaging.outgoing.barista.health-startup-enabled=false\nmp.messaging.outgoing.kitchen.health-readiness-enabled=false\nmp.messaging.outgoing.kitchen.health-startup-enabled=false","new_string":"# Health check - serve at /health (under non-application root /)\nquarkus.http.non-application-root-path=/\nquarkus.smallrye-health.root-path=health\n\n# Disable ALL SmallRye Reactive Messaging health checks (liveness, readiness, startup)\n# so that Kafka unavailability does not mark the app DOWN\nsmallrye.messaging.health.channel-enabled=false\nmp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.health-enabled=false\nmp.messaging.outgoing.barista.health-enabled=false\nmp.messaging.outgoing.kitchen.health-enabled=false\nquarkus.kafka.health.enabled=false"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1546,"cache_read_input_tokens":81172,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1546,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":548},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c8c0436c-69f4-4378-aa8f-dd3eb0ddb087",