{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_013tNs71JTBzyiLahNefbMCm","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The validation error is still `@NotBlank` on `String`. This is bizarre - `@NotBlank` should absolutely work with `String`. The error `No validator could be found for constraint 'jakarta.validation.constraints.NotBlank' validating type 'java.lang.String'` suggests the Hibernate Validator is not properly configured or there's a classloader issue.\n\nWait - this might be a dependency issue. The `common` module has `jakarta.validation-api` but might be missing the hibernate-validator implementation. Let me check the common pom:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":469,"cache_read_input_tokens":85744,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":469,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":232},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c8c0436c-69f4-4378-aa8f-dd3eb0ddb087","uuid":"945ed52c-9ceb-4549-8080-b967e58bcac4"}
