{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_0114JGBxERZnwCn39KwG9f9g","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Same issue with `@Size`. This strongly suggests that Quarkus's build-time validator optimization is removing the standard validators. The issue is likely that the `OrderRequest` class is in the `common` module which is NOT processed by Quarkus's annotation processing.\n\nThe fix: since `common` is a plain JAR module (not a Quarkus module), Quarkus doesn't index it for Bean Validation at build time. I need to add a Jandex index to the `common` module, or add the `quarkus.index-dependency` property.\n\nLet me add the index dependency config:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":387,"cache_read_input_tokens":91138,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":387,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":251},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c8c0436c-69f4-4378-aa8f-dd3eb0ddb087","uuid":"88bb28ac-db6e-42aa-b04d-2be90cea2cfe"}
