{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014hk89oyUmwvoNT1FDnvijx","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Quarkus HTTP\n     2→quarkus.http.port=8080\n     3→\n     4→# ===== Default: H2 in-memory (standalone/testing) =====\n     5→quarkus.datasource.db-kind=h2\n     6→quarkus.datasource.jdbc.url=jdbc:h2:mem:coffeeshop;DB_CLOSE_DELAY=-1\n     7→quarkus.datasource.username=sa\n     8→quarkus.datasource.password=\n     9→\n    10→# ===== \"pg\" profile: PostgreSQL (activate with -Dquarkus.profile=pg) =====\n    11→%pg.quarkus.datasource.db-kind=postgresql\n    12→%pg.quarkus.datasource.jdbc.url=jdbc:postgresql://${DB_HOST:localhost}:${DB_PORT:5432}/${DB_NAME:coffeeshop}\n    13→%pg.quarkus.datasource.username=${DB_USER:cafe}\n    14→%pg.quarkus.datasource.password=${DB_PASSWORD:cafe}\n    15→\n    16→# Hibernate ORM\n    17→quarkus.hibernate-orm.database.generation=drop-and-create\n    18→quarkus.hibernate-orm.log.sql=false\n    19→\n    20→# Kafka bootstrap\n    21→kafka.bootstrap.servers=${KAFKA_BOOTSTRAP:localhost:9092}\n    22→\n    23→# --- outgoing: barista commands ---\n    24→mp.messaging.outgoing.barista.connector=smallrye-kafka\n    25→mp.messaging.outgoing.barista.topic=barista-commands\n    26→mp.messaging.outgoing.barista.value.serializer=org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.StringSerializer\n    27→mp.messaging.outgoing.barista.lazy-client=true\n    28→\n    29→# --- outgoing: kitchen commands ---\n    30→mp.messaging.outgoing.kitchen.connector=smallrye-kafka\n    31→mp.messaging.outgoing.kitchen.topic=kitchen-commands\n    32→mp.messaging.outgoing.kitchen.value.serializer=org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.StringSerializer\n    33→mp.messaging.outgoing.kitchen.lazy-client=true\n    34→\n    35→# --- incoming: order updates ---\n    36→mp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.connector=smallrye-kafka\n    37→mp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.topic=order-updates\n    38→mp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.value.deserializer=org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.StringDeserializer\n    39→mp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.group.id=orders-service\n    40→mp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.auto.offset.reset=latest\n    41→mp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.failure-strategy=ignore\n    42→mp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.lazy-client=true\n    43→mp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.retry=true\n    44→mp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.retry.max-wait=60\n    45→\n    46→# Health check - serve at /health (under non-application root /)\n    47→quarkus.http.non-application-root-path=/\n    48→quarkus.smallrye-health.root-path=health\n    49→\n    50→# Disable ALL SmallRye Reactive Messaging health checks (liveness, readiness, startup)\n    51→# so that Kafka unavailability does not mark the app DOWN\n    52→smallrye.messaging.health.channel-enabled=false\n    53→mp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.health-enabled=false\n    54→mp.messaging.outgoing.barista.health-enabled=false\n    55→mp.messaging.outgoing.kitchen.health-enabled=false\n    56→quarkus.kafka.health.enabled=false\n    57→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c8c0436c-69f4-4378-aa8f-dd3eb0ddb087","uuid":"bdc959b1-3214-41e3-88b3-3588ea48829a"}
